A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating and commending Youth Villages; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Youth Villages was founded in 1986 and has built a national reputation for
3 radically improving the lives of America's children, families, and young adults; and
4 WHEREAS, Youth Villages is recognized as a leader in providing, partnering with others,
5 and advocating for innovative, evidence-based, family-focused program models and services
6 designed to preserve and restore families as well as help children reach for their dreams,
7 bettering the lives of more than 43,000 youth annually in 27 states and the District of
8 Columbia across 102 locations in 2024; and
9 WHEREAS, the mission of Youth Villages is to "help children and families live
10 successfully," and the organization adheres to its values, including that "kids' needs come
11 firstâ€¦always," believing that every child should have the resources and opportunities they
12 need; and
13 WHEREAS, Youth Villages began its operations in Georgia in 2009, marking 15 years of
14 service in the state in 2024, during which it helped more than 5,500 children, families, and
15 young adults; and
