16 WHEREAS, Youth Villages serves Georgia's children and their families through its Inner
17 Harbour Campus, a psychiatric residential treatment facility in Douglasville, and it is
18 elevating residential services in the state with $70 million in new construction and
19 renovations at the facility; and
20 WHEREAS, Youth Villages provides community-based services in the metro Atlanta area
21 through its Intercept program, an integrated intensive in-home program proven to safely
22 prevent children from entering foster care or to reunite families quickly when out-of-home
23 care is required, and through its LifeSet model, which serves as a bridge to successful
24 adulthood for young people who have experienced foster care or other childhood trauma; and
25 WHEREAS, Youth Villages has been honored by numerous organizations and agencies,
26 including being certified as a Great Place to Work and recognized by the White House as a
27 "high-impact, results-oriented organization"; and
28 WHEREAS, Youth Villages partners with the Georgia Departments of Behavioral Health
29 and Developmental Disabilities, Community Health, Education, and Human Services to
30 serve Georgia's children, families, and young adults; and
31 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
32 distinguished organization, its staff, and its volunteers be appropriately recognized for their
33 dedication and work to better the lives of Georgia's children, young adults, and their families.
34 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
35 the members of this body congratulate Youth Villages, its staff, and its volunteers and
36 convey to them this legislative body's heartiest commendation for their past, present, and
